# Finite State Machine (FSM)

## Aim
To understand and implement a Finite State Machine in digital electronics.

## Introduction
Finite State Machine (FSM) is a sequential circuit used to control digital systems. It changes states based on input signals and clock pulses.

## Project Description
This project demonstrates a simple Traffic Light Controller using FSM.

### States
- S0 → Red Light ON
- S1 → Yellow Light ON
- S2 → Green Light ON

### State Flow
Red → Yellow → Green → Red

## Components Used
- Logic Gates
- Flip-Flops
- Clock Pulse

## Applications
- Traffic light systems
- Sequence detector
- Digital counters

## Conclusion
Finite State Machine helps in designing sequential digital systems efficiently.
